description.narrative: To improve the quality and opportunity in secondary education by: a. Increasing access to general secondary education through upgrading commercial schools to technological general schools and providing flexible options for study within and between branches of the system; b. Better aligning curricula and assessment with the skills needs of employers and higher education; c. Providing professional development for teachers and administrators on new technologies, curricula, assessment and management techniques; and d. Strengthening institutional capacity.

condition.narrative: Borrower shall furnish Association no later than 6 months after closing, a plan for the future operation of the project
Policies & procedures for monitoring & evaluation and an M & E report for activites before covenant due date.

title.narrative: A core curriculum framework developed, including the curriculum for core subject areas

target.value: Core and elective curriculum and textbooks developed for general and technical education

actual.value: A new curriculum framework was prepared by the Ministry of Education Team and presented to the Minister for approval.

title.narrative: At least 70% of school management teams in project schools are judged competent in duties as outlined in new job criteria by 2012

baseline.value: No performance measurement criteria are available

target.value: Management competence of 70% of management teams meets standards of efficiency and effectiveness in SEEP schools

comment.narrative: Only level one and two evaluation has been done. No level three evaluation has been conducted to assess the extent that the newlytrained managers are managing schools differently; using the newly acquired know-how; and meeting standards of efficiency andeffectiveness.

title.narrative: Board of Trustees set up in all project schools

baseline.value: Schools do not have Board of Trustees

target.value: All project schools have active Board of Trustees.

actual.value: All project schools have Board of Trustees

comment.narrative: No systematic evaluation of the operation of the school BOT has been carried out. However, evidence collected by the World Bankschool score pilot indicates that BOT are actively supporting schools in the development of school improvement plans.

title.narrative: Share of general secondary students increases from 30% to 40% by 2010
School Administrators in project schools are competent in the use of ICT for enhanced school management

comment.narrative: Only level one evaluation of ICT training programs has been conducted, therefore there is only anecdotal evidence regarding thedegree that school administrators are using ICT or not.

title.narrative: At least 30% of project schools comply with minimum accreditation standards with respect to infrastructure and learning equipment

actual.value: A total of 53 (26%) project schools are under rehabilitation. Phase one has been completed for 20 of these schools

title.narrative: Core subject matter teachers in participating schools master the new curriculum framework

baseline.value: No teacher has been trained in new curriculum framework

target.value: 11,000 teachers in participating schools trained in new curriculum

comment.narrative: Teachers are being trained in new teaching methodologies that are contemplated as part of the new curriculum framework
